quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  98,8,"Their reward with their Lord is Gardens of Eternity under which rivers flow, abiding therein forever. Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. This is for those who fear their Lord.",""
  99,1,"When the earth is shaken with a mighty quake,",""
  99,2,"and the earth throws out its burdens<sup>1</sup>,","[1] i.e., its dead bodies and treasures."
  99,3,"and man says<sup>2</sup>, “What is the matter with it?”","[2] In terror and astonishment."
  99,4,"On that Day it will recount all its news,",""
  99,5,"because your Lord has inspired it [to do so].",""
  99,6,"On that Day all people will come forward in separate groups to be shown their deeds<sup>3</sup>.","[3] From the place of Judgment to see the consequences of their deeds, whether to Paradise or to Hell.\n [MMCXIII]"
  99,7,"So whoever does an atom’s weight<sup>4</sup> of good will see it,","[4] Or a small ant’s weight."
  99,8,"and whoever does an atom’s weight of evil will see it.",""
  100,1,"By the galloping, panting horses<sup>1</sup>,","[1] i.e., those horses that fight for the cause of Allah as they race to attack the enemy."
  100,2,"striking sparks of fire [with their hooves]<sup>2</sup>,","[2] While galloping over rocky terrain."
  100,3,"launching raids at dawn<sup>3</sup>,","[3] While the enemy is unaware of their raid."
  100,4,"stirring up thereby clouds of dust,",""
  100,5,"plunging thereby into the midst of the enemy<sup>4</sup>,","[4] i.e., penetrating into the ranks of the enemy as a surprise attack."
  100,6,"indeed, man is very ungrateful to his Lord<sup>5</sup> –","[5] disobeying Him by not spending in the cause of Allah from what He has given him and commanded him to spend accordingly."
  100,7,"and he himself is a witness to that<sup>6</sup> –","[6] By his words and actions."
  100,8,"and he is truly extreme in his love of wealth.",""
  100,9,"Does he not know that when the contents of graves will be overturned,",""
